-- Santander Brasil to Sell $800 Million of 5-Year Bonds Today
-- B y   V e r o n i c a   N a v a r r o   E s p i n o s a   a n d   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-02-06T19:10:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/santander-brasil-to-sell-benchmark-five-year-dollar-bonds-today.html
Banco Santander Brasil SA, the
Brazilian unit of  Spain ’s largest bank, plans to sell $800
million of five-year bonds as soon as today, according to a
person familiar with the transaction.  The bank may sell the bonds to yield 400 basis points, or 4
percentage points, more than U.S. Treasuries, said the person,
who asked not to be identified because terms aren’t set. Bank of
America Corp., BNP Paribas SA, Banco Santander SA and Standard
Chartered Bank are managing the sale, according to the person.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Veronica Navarro Espinosa in New York at 
 vespinosa@bloomberg.net ;
Esteban Duarte in Madrid  at 
